<ns1501:section xmlns:ns1501="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="resources.information.technologies.java.j2ee.ejb.enterpriseBeans.entityBeans.introduction.objectView">

  <ns1502:title xmlns:ns1502="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Entity beans provide an object view onto persistent information</ns1502:title>
  <ns1503:para xmlns:ns1503="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    Entity beans supply an object view which is completely decoupled from the structure
    of the underlying persistent storage (e.g. database structure). The object attributes
    could all be located in a single row of a database. Alternatively they may be assembled
    from different fields of different tables or even from different databases.
  </ns1503:para>
</ns1501:section>